DESCRIPTION:Join us on Saturday\, February 21\, from 1–3 PM at Whispering Vine Fourth Street for an extraordinary afternoon dedicated to Napa Valley and West Coast Cabernet Sauvignon\, featuring a rare lineup of iconic producers and benchmark bottlings\, paired with freshly prepared flatbread.\nTasting Fee: $85 per person (Includes flatbread and a tasting of all featured wines)\nLimited to 50 guests\nReserve your Spot\nFeatured Wines:\n• Silver Oak Alexander Valley Cabernet Sauvignon 2018 – 94 pts James Suckling\, 93 pts Wine Spectator – Polished and expressive with ripe blackberry\, cassis\, sweet oak\, cedar\, and a long\, savory finish.\n• Groth Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon 2021 – 96 pts Wine Spectator\, 95 pts Robert Parker’s Wine Advocate – Sleek and age-worthy\, delivering pure cassis\, blackberry\, licorice\, cedar\, and wet slate with remarkable precision and length.\n• Anthem Mt. Veeder Estate Cabernet Sauvignon 2019 – Powerful and mountain-driven with dark cherry\, blackberry\, olive\, bay leaf\, espresso\, and a long\, structured finish.\n• Paul Hobbs Coombsville Cabernet Sauvignon 2022 – 96 pts James Suckling\, 94 pts Decanter – Layered and refined with cherry\, cassis\, violets\, savory spice\, and silky tannins framed by cool-climate freshness.\n• Caymus Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon 2023 – Lush and signature in style\, offering deep color\, ripe berry fruit\, cocoa\, and supple\, approachable tannins.\n• Justin Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon 2022 – Concentrated and structured with blackberry\, cassis\, espresso\, cedar\, and a long\, polished finish.\n• Heitz Cellar Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon 2021 – 99 pts Decanter – Remarkably pure and tightly focused with pristine black fruit\, violet aromatics\, and mineral-driven tannins built for longevity.\n• Adaptation by Odette Cabernet Sauvignon 2019 – Seamless and elegant with blackberry\, crème de cassis\, cocoa\, espresso\, and impressive balance.\n• Faust Cabernet Sauvignon 2023 – Bold yet refined with Luxardo cherry\, blueberry compote\, dark cocoa\, forest floor\, and fine-grained tannins.\n• Clos du Val Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon 2022 – 96 pts Tasting Panel – Sleek and impeccably balanced with plum\, black olive\, slate\, fig\, and savory tea notes.\n• Turnbull Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon 2023 – Fresh and vibrant with red plum\, blackberry compote\, sagebrush\, baking spice\, and lively acidity.\nAn unparalleled opportunity to taste an elite collection of Cabernet Sauvignons side by side—a must-attend event for serious Cabernet lovers and collectors alike.
LOCATION:4201 W Fourth St Reno\, NV 89523
